<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1823,2029]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1860,1885]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1853" box="[280,455,1860,1885]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hilaris">
<emphasis box="[280,455,1860,1885]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Andrena hilaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first recorded from 
<collectingRegion box="[732,840,1860,1885]" country="United States of America" name="Michigan" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Michigan</collectingRegion>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mitchell" box="[881,1061,1860,1885]" firstAuthor="Mitchell" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 538" refId="ref96571" refString="Mitchell, T. B. (1960) Bees of the Eastern United States: volume I. N. C. Agricultural Experimental Station Technical Bulletin, 141, 1 - 538." type="book chapter" year="1960">Mitchell (1960)</bibRefCitation>
. No specimens from 
<collectingRegion box="[1298,1405,1860,1885]" country="United States of America" name="Michigan" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Michigan</collectingRegion>
or neighboring states were examined by Bouseman &amp; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bouseman, J. K. &amp; LaBerge, W. E." box="[768,951,1896,1920]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="275 - 389" refId="ref84124" refString="Bouseman, J. K. &amp; LaBerge, W. E. (1979) A revision of the bees of the genus Andrena of the Western Hemisphere. Part IX. Subgenus Melandrena. Transactions of the American Entomological Society ,, 104, 275 - 389." type="journal article" year="1979">LaBerge (1978)</bibRefCitation>
and they refer to it as a relatively rare, southeastern species. Four male Dreisbach specimens identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1853" box="[940,1048,1932,1957]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hilaris">
<emphasis box="[940,957,1932,1955]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[975,1048,1932,1957]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">hilaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were found at MSUC, but upon examination by JG were found to be 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1853" box="[591,701,1968,1993]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nivalis">
<emphasis box="[591,608,1969,1992]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[626,701,1968,1993]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">nivalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1853" box="[719,898,1968,1993]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hilaris">
<emphasis box="[719,898,1968,1993]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Andrena hilaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does occur in 
<collectingRegion box="[1076,1186,1968,1993]" country="United States of America" name="Michigan" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Michigan</collectingRegion>
, based on three male specimens collected from a single site in Allegan County (
<bibRefCitation author="Tuell" box="[805,995,2004,2029]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Tuell" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="275 - 287" refId="ref105004" refString="Tuell, J. K., Ascher, J. S. &amp; Isaacs, R. (2009) Wild bees (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophila) of the Michigan highbush blueberry agroecosystem. Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 102, 275 - 287. https: // doi. org / 10.1603 / 008.102.0209" type="journal article" year="2009">
Tuell 
<emphasis box="[871,928,2004,2029]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
